{
  "doc_id": "26188",
  "text": "Hypertension (HTN) is one of the most important risk factors that can lead to cardiovascular diseases (CVD) and is thus regarded as a serious public health problem. The prevalence of HTN has been increasing in most areas worldwide, especially in developing countries [CITATION_1] . Studies in Iran have also shown a high incidence of the condition [CITATION_2] . A previous study from this area showed that almost one-third of the CVD events and 27% of mortalities ensued from HTN, indicating the highest attributable risks [CITATION_3] . The presence of other risk factors such as insulin resistance, dyslipidemia, obesity, and metabolic syndrome increases the HTN's harmful impact on target organs and CVD risk [CITATION_4] .",
